pr_body:
- make pcap.Reader's fileobj STDIN and [c]StringIO compatible;
- fix a dispatch() issue #105 and make it closer to pypcap implementation (took the docstring from there);
- add unit tests.

WIP - Cancel now works, but retriggering doesn't for some reason yet.

Removed converting the response to a ``JobModel`` object because we don't use the object, so it's just a waste of time.  The object is also not returned from the ``retrigger`` or ``cancel`` endpoints.  It just returns:

    {"message":"All jobs successfully retriggered."}

@birdage I made a re-write of the changelog using the command:

`git log --no-merges --pretty=format:"- %s (%an %h)"`

Review and merge please :smile_cat:

- This PR adds a test to make sure the `DataSet` can be used with a custom loop (e.g. without the qocdes `Loop`).
- It also autopeps some of the other test functions.

@unga @core

The following works now

```python
import ray

ray.worker._init(start_ray_local=True, num_local_schedulers=2, use_raylet=True, resources=[{'Custom1': 1}, {'Custom2': 1}])

@ray.remote(resources={'Custom1': 1})
def f():
    return 1

@ray.remote(resources={'Custom2': 1})
def g():
    return 1

ray.get([f.remote(), g.remote()])
```
